---
title: Convert to the @nx/cypress inferred plugin
description: Migrate off the deprecated @nx/cypress:cypress executor by using the @nx/cypress/plugin inferred targets.
sidebar:
  label: Convert to the inferred plugin
filter: 'type:Guides'
---

The `@nx/cypress:cypress` executor is deprecated and will be removed in **Nx v24**. The `@nx/cypress/plugin` inferred plugin produces equivalent `e2e` and `component-test` targets directly from your `cypress.config.*` file, with no executor wrapper. This guide walks through converting existing executor-based targets to the inferred plugin.

Your Cypress configuration (`cypress.config.ts` / `.js`) does not need to change.

## Auto-convert (recommended)

Run the included generator:

```shell
nx g @nx/cypress:convert-to-inferred
```

This:

- Removes `@nx/cypress:cypress` executor targets from each project
- Ensures `@nx/cypress/plugin` is registered in `nx.json` with the right target-name overrides
- Preserves any per-target options (configurations, watch mode, baseUrl, dev-server target, etc.) that the inferred plugin can't represent directly

After it runs, the `e2e` and `component-test` targets on each project come from the inferred plugin.

## Manual setup

If you'd rather wire it yourself, add the plugin to `nx.json`:

```json
// nx.json
{
  "plugins": [
    {
      "plugin": "@nx/cypress/plugin",
      "options": {
        "targetName": "e2e",
        "componentTestingTargetName": "component-test"
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

Then remove the explicit `e2e` (and any `component-test`) targets from each project — the inferred plugin creates them automatically for any project that has a `cypress.config.*` file.

## What stays the same

- `cypress` itself remains a peer dependency of `@nx/cypress` and continues to work normally.
- The `@nx/cypress` package and the `@nx/cypress/plugin` inferred plugin remain supported.
- The `@nx/cypress:configuration` and `@nx/cypress:component-configuration` scaffolding generators keep working. New scaffolds emit no executor-based targets when the inferred plugin is registered.
